{"type":"message","id":"e0e85e08","parentId":"dcb907d7","timestamp":"2026-03-07T22:16:11.398Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user is greeting me via the OpenClaw TUI (gateway client). This is a simple hello message. Based on my SOUL.md and AGENTS.md, I should:\n\n1. Be personal and warm in direct conversations\n2. Have a personality - dry wit, slightly sardonic, but friendly\n3. Reference the \"lobster\" identity subtly if it fits\n4. Not be overly formal or stiff\n\nSince this is a direct chat (webchat channel), I can be more casual and personal. The user just said \"hello\" - simple greeting deserves a friendly response that shows I'm here and ready to help, but with some personality.\n\nLet me craft a response that:\n- Acknowledges the greeting warmly\n- Shows I'm ready to help\n- Has a bit of personality (maybe a subtle lobster reference or just keep it friendly)\n- Keeps it concise but not terse\n\nGiven the time is 6:16 AM on a Sunday in Singapore, I could make a gentle joke about the early hour while being welcoming","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Hey. You're up early for a Sunday — or is this a \"can't sleep, might as well check on things\" moment?\n\nI'm here and ready whenever you are. What's on your mind?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":17967,"output":253,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18220,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772921763648}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba61aeeb","parentId":"e0e85e08","timestamp":"2026-03-07T22:17:43.890Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 06:17 GMT+8] please update \n Based on the previous analysis table and current workspace state, here's the implementation status: \n \n Implementation Status Update \n \n | Task | Planned State | Current State | Status | \n |------|---------------|-------- -------|--------| \n | anchor-v2.sh | Full QMD integration with --save, filtering modes | ❌ Not found | 🔴 Not started | \n | context-recover.sh | Semantic wrapper calling anchor --semantic | ✅ Exists (Mar 3) | 🟡 Verify implementation | \n | qmd embed | 4 docs, 5 chunks embedded | ✅ Verified | ✅ Complete | \n | AGENTS.md | Add anchor.sh to startup routine | ❌ Not updated | 🔴 Pending | \n \n Summary: \n - context-recover.sh exists (created March 3) but need to verify it has proper semantic wrapper functionality \n - anchor-v2.sh doesn't appear to exist yet — the stub may not have been created \n \n\n Let me check the current workspace state and verify what's implemented vs. what still needs work. \n Just checked the workspace from that earlier status update: \n \n Current State: \n - context-recover.sh ✅ Exists and properly implemented — semantic wrapper with --semantic flag for QMD integration \n - anchor-v2.sh ❌ Still doesn't exist — never got created \n - AGENTS.md ❌ Not updated — still missing the anchor startup routine \n \n So we've got the wrapper, but the actual anchor.sh core script and the AGENTS.md integration never happened."}],"timestamp":1772921863888}}
